-- Bulgarian economy to grow by 2.1 pct in 2014
-- By Angel Krasimirov
-- Fri Apr 04, 2014 05:01AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, April 4 (Reuters) - Bulgaria's gross domestic product is expected to grow by 2.1 percent this year, against an original forecast of 1.8 percent, Finance Minister Petar Chobanov said on Friday.

